    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 98,
        "summary": "Sing unto the Lord\u2014All the ends of the earth will see His salvation\u2014He comes to judge all men with equity and righteousness.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "O sing unto the Lord a new song; for he hath done marvellous things: his right hand, and his holy arm, hath gotten him the victory.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Singing.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 15:6 (1\u201312).",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord hath made known his salvation: his righteousness hath he openly shewed in the sight of the heathen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 62:2.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 26:45.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 15:13; D&C 90:10 (10\u201311).",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He hath remembered his mercy and his truth toward the house of Israel: all the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 24:27; 3\u00a0Ne. 5:21 (21\u201326).",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Make a joyful noise unto the Lord, all the earth: make a loud noise, and rejoice, and sing praise.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0burst into song.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Sing unto the Lord with the harp; with the harp, and the voice of a psalm.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "With trumpets and sound of cornet make a joyful noise before the Lord, the King.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof; the world, and they that dwell therein.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the floods clap their hands: let the hills be joyful together",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Before the Lord; for he cometh to judge the earth: with righteousness shall he judge the world, and the people with equity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 22:21 (21\u201324); Moses 6:57.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0World.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
